Done. I reviewed the forum topic about the wrong working directory bug. The design document already explicitly covers the correct behavior in its "Project Directory" section — `run_bot.sh` must `cd` to the project root, and Python code should use `Path.cwd()` rather than `__file__` parent-directory arithmetic. The root cause identified by QA matches exactly the anti-pattern the design warns against. No design changes are needed; this is purely an implementation fix. I added a comment confirming this and voted to close.
